Saudi February PMI Drops to 63.4 From 63.8, SAAB-HSBC Data Show

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-03-05T13:47:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/saudi-february-pmi-drops-to-63-4-from-63-8-saab-hsbc-data-show.html
  Saudi Arabia ’s purchasing managers
index fell to 63.4 points in February from 63.8 in January,
according to the SABB HSBC Purchasing Managers’ Index.  The report reflects the economic performance of Saudi
Arabian non-oil producing private sector companies and firms, it
said.  Input prices rose to a record as costs of fuel and raw
materials increased, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  